cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely sub-category as the paper focuses on the use of CNNs in image classification and the presence of spatially agglomerative local-to-global interactions within the data. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the impact of adding convolutional layers to a CNN and the synchronization of feature map spatial orderness during training. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the use of CNNs in various domains and proposes a statistical metric to quantify the extent to which input data obeys the underlying spatial ordering. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with the analysis of network weights and the impact of kernel size on spatial orderness. 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely sub-category as the paper does not explicitly deal with natural language processing, but the discussion of spatially agglomerative interactions may have some relevance to language modeling.
